            <title><![CDATA[Life is Strange: Reunion Shares PC Specs That Are Nearly Identical to Double Exposure]]></title>
            <link>https://wccftech.com/life-is-strange-reunion-pc-specs-nearly-identical-double-exposure/</link>
            <guid>1465864</guid>
            <content:encoded><![CDATA[<div id="readability-page-1" class="page"><div>

			

			
			
			
			
			<p>With eight days left before the <a href="https://wccftech.com/life-is-strange-reunion-emotional-conclusion-max-chloe-march-26/" type="link" id="https://wccftech.com/life-is-strange-reunion-emotional-conclusion-max-chloe-march-26/" target="_blank" rel="noreferrer noopener">launch of <strong>Life is Strange: Reunion</strong></a>, developer <strong>Deck Nine Games</strong> and publisher <strong>Square Enix</strong> have shared the detailed PC specifications, and on the surface, they're surprisingly high for this type of game. You'll need an NVIDIA GeForce RTX 4080 or AMD Radeon 7900 XTX to play with the highest preset, "<strong>Hella High</strong>", at 4K and 30 frames per second.</p>



<p>However, looking back to the previous franchise installment, <strong>2024's <a href="https://wccftech.com/review/life-is-strange-double-exposure-drawn-out-murder-mystery/" type="link" id="https://wccftech.com/review/life-is-strange-double-exposure-drawn-out-murder-mystery/" target="_blank" rel="noreferrer noopener">Life is Strange: Double Exposure</a></strong>, <strong>the specs are nearly identical</strong>. That game required the same GPUs to play at the highest preset, then simply called "<strong>Cinematic</strong>", at 4K@30FPS. So, this is nothing new for those who already got Double Exposure.</p>



<figure><table><thead><tr><th data-align="left">SPECS</th><th data-align="left">MINIMUM</th><th data-align="left">RECOMMENDED</th><th data-align="left">PERFORMANCE</th><th data-align="left">ULTRA</th><th data-align="left">HELLA HIGH</th></tr></thead><tbody><tr><td data-align="left"><strong>OS</strong></td><td data-align="left">Windows 10</td><td data-align="left">Windows 11</td><td data-align="left">Windows 11</td><td data-align="left">Windows 11</td><td data-align="left">Windows 11</td></tr><tr><td data-align="left"><strong>CPU</strong></td><td data-align="left">AMD Ryzen 5 1400 / Intel Core i5-4670K</td><td data-align="left">AMD Ryzen 5 3600 / Intel Core i5-10600</td><td data-align="left">AMD Ryzen 7 3700X / Intel Core i5-12600K</td><td data-align="left">AMD Ryzen 7 3700X / Intel Core i5-12600</td><td data-align="left">AMD Ryzen 7 5800X / Intel Core i7-13700K</td></tr><tr><td data-align="left"><strong>Memory</strong></td><td data-align="left">12GB RAM</td><td data-align="left">16GB RAM</td><td data-align="left">16GB RAM</td><td data-align="left">16GB RAM</td><td data-align="left">16GB RAM</td></tr><tr><td data-align="left"><strong>GPU</strong></td><td data-align="left">AMD Radeon RX 480 8GB / NVIDIA GeForce GTX 1660 6GB / Intel Arc A750 8GB</td><td data-align="left">AMD Radeon RX 6650 XT 8GB / NVIDIA GeForce RTX 3060 12GB</td><td data-align="left">AMD Radeon RX 6700 XT 12GB / NVIDIA GeForce RTX 3070 8GB</td><td data-align="left">AMD Radeon RX 6900 XT 16GB / NVIDIA GeForce RTX 3080 10GB</td><td data-align="left">AMD Radeon RX 7900 XTX 24GB / NVIDIA GeForce RTX 4080 16GB</td></tr><tr><td data-align="left"><strong>DirectX</strong></td><td data-align="left">Version 12, Feature Level 12_0</td><td data-align="left">Version 12, Feature Level 12_0</td><td data-align="left">Version 12, Feature Level 12_0</td><td data-align="left">Version 12, Feature Level 12_0</td><td data-align="left">Version 12, Feature Level 12_0</td></tr><tr><td data-align="left"><strong>Details</strong></td><td data-align="left">Low 1080p @ 30 FPS</td><td data-align="left">High 1080p @ 60 FPS</td><td data-align="left">High 1440p @ 60 FPS</td><td data-align="left">High 2160p @ 60 FPS</td><td data-align="left">Hella High 2160p @ 30 FPS</td></tr><tr><td data-align="left"><strong>Storage</strong></td><td data-align="left">30GB</td><td data-align="left">30GB</td><td data-align="left">30GB</td><td data-align="left">30GB</td><td data-align="left">30GB</td></tr></tbody></table></figure>



<p>Life is Strange: Reunion brings back Chloe Price, <strong>finally concluding the saga of Max and Chloe</strong> as well as the fate of Caledon, with players able to influence the ending with their decisions. </p>



<p>In other franchise news, the two characters <strong><a href="https://wccftech.com/life-is-strange-tv-series-max-chloe-cast-maisy-stella-tatum-grace-hopkins/" type="link" id="https://wccftech.com/life-is-strange-tv-series-max-chloe-cast-maisy-stella-tatum-grace-hopkins/" target="_blank" rel="noreferrer noopener">have recently been cast for Amazon's upcoming TV series adaptation</a></strong>: Maisy Stella will play Chloe, while Tatum Grace Hopkins will play Max.</p>

			
			
